n</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/9/01 3:48:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> EK is generally where I go, mainly because it's easy to reach. I have heard the spiders in Guk are good too. It used to be the spiders in S Ro were a good option too, but I have found once I clear them all, they seem to be on a cycle where they don't come back for a while. You don't really need tracking, you can see spiders a long way off...tag 3-4 with your flux staff and hit them with Jylls, it goes pretty quick. <p><table><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udiomedes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diomedes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/01 9:20:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> heart spiders in upper guk no contest.<br><br>there are 14 spiders total if memory serves. while crag spiders may drop silks more frequently there are 2 reasons why heart spiders are 100 times better than crag spiders<br><br>1. its a camp - dont need to run around trying to be first to a roamer - dont have to worry about killing mobs on the same spawn table to keep the spawn rotating - you are guaranteed 14 spiders every 15ish minutes.<br><br>2. its a safe camp - sit far back enough in the first &quot;alcove&quot; (where the giant spider spawns) and nothing will aggro you. This means you can go afk between spawns if you want without fear that youll get jumped. Lets face it, farming silk is a seriously boring proposition - you may as well not let that stop you from watching something on TV or doing something else while you wait.<br><br>you can clear all 14 spawns in 3 fights - 10 spawns upstairs, 4 spawns on the &quot;bridge&quot; area - above the water where the skeletal monk for acumen mask spawns.<br><br>IMO anyone who would say that EK is best is trying to keep upper guk a &quot;secret&quot;. Dont be mislead - EK is only better if you have sow and tracking and can stand the tedium of doing something mundane over and over and over again. <p><font face="verdana" size="2">[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=85843" target="new"><b>Diomedes</b></a></font> (High Elf) <font face="verdana" size="2"><font face="verdana" size="2">&lt;The Vagrants&gt; ZONE:ezboard</font><br><b><font face="verdana" size="2">The Tribunal</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utwiddleotoole.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiddle OToole</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_bullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/01 8:59:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_thumb.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> Yes, but you have to admit it's fun to PBAoE the gnolls by the ramp to Highpass every 10 minutes or so when you're in EK.  I haven't checked, but I may actually not be KoS to the Karana bandits anymore.  Plus you get scalps you can turn in in Highpass for several good factions, including Freeport Militia, if I recall correctly.  I might be thinking of Highkeep goblin ears though.<br><br>I'm a silly person when it comes to faction...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><table> <tr>  <td style=filter:glow(color=#303870 strength=1)>   <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=5665" style=text-decoration:none><font size=2 color=#6070E0>Twiddle O`Toole</font></a>   <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bruneofwar35127" style=text-decoration:none><font size=2 color=#6070E0>&lt;Rune of War&gt;</font></a>  </td>  <td valign=bottom>   <font size=1>    &nbsp;  <i>54 <strike>Channeler</strike> Cabbie / Veeshan</i>   </font>  </td> </tr></table><table> <tr>  <td>   <font size=1>    <i>(175 Smith; 168 Researcher; 168 Brewer; 167 Fisherman; 164 Beggar; 148 Potter; 142 Baker; 123 Tailor; 35 Jeweler)</i><br>    <font color=#F00000>Twiddle scowls at you, ready to attack -- what would you like his tombstone to say?</font>   </font>  </td> </tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fredre>Fredre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/01 8:52:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I would have to say EK.  While it does sound like Guk would be better (haven't been there myself), I prefer EK several additional reasons.  One, there are a bunch of lions running around and the HQ pelts can get you to 115 with quivers and the ruined ones can be used to make poison vials (+ pearl + 'chanter friend + silk) can make Wu's armor which get into the upper 140's, IIRC.  Two, there are the occasional HG's that wander about which are good for XP (well at least for me) and cash.  Occasionally you have to clean out the crawlers and hounds, since the number of them seems inversely proportional to the number of lions and spiders.<br><br>Fredre &lt;Adamant Sentinal of Ro&gt; 44th Wizard<br>Druzzil Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usbrobin24.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sbrobin24</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/01 7:08:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> &quot;heart spiders in upper guk no contest.&quot;<br><br>I contest.   I tried EK at level 50. I tried guk at 50.  Didn't have enough mana to kill all the spiders in guk until I got that static pulse spell.  I took my 45 necro to EK and there are MUCH more spiders. Sure, you have to run around, but you can get many more silks.   14 spiders every 18 mins is less than the 18 crags I can kill in EK in 18 mins, especially since crags drop more silk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/6/01 10:55:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I should add that in EK, if you kill snakes as well as spiders, you'll get more spiders to spawn. They seem to be on the same spawn table.<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualurarz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alura RZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/8/01 1:15:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> Using 2 computers, I had a wizard camping at EK, and I had a warrior camped at l guk killing all heart spider spawns.  I'm not sure how long the time was but I reached 8 stacks of spider silk in EK before I reached 6 stacks in l guk, even though 1) I didn't kill all the available spiders in EK, 2) think this is statistically significant.  <br><br>EK Crag spiders just drop alot of spider silks  thank heart spiders.  Of course this changes if there is a druid camping spiders too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyaldin111.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaldin111</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/24/01 1:48:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> Lguk deadly black widows, low 20's spiders, generally get 2 silks off of em but its a linear camp, they're not hard and there's lots of em and it's hardly ever camped.  Got a ton of silks this way.<br><br>Yaldin<br>55 Evoker<br>Karana Server<br>Storm`s Justice <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobiquon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obiquon1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/8/02 10:12:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> EK is great, kill spiders (I've had some drop 8 silks) then kill lions (for pelts) while waiting for the spiders to respawn. You can farm here all day.<br><br>Oh, the random HG makes a nice change of pace and gets you a litlle loot.<br> <p><br><br><center><img src="http://www.magicalcheese.com/uploads/obiquon/obisig2.jpg"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68512" target="_blank">[ I got a bad feeling about this ]</a> <br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 2:11:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> From my experience:<br><br>53+ wizard:  uguk heart spiders (jylls works wonders)<br>Bard or druid: EK (tracking, sow/selos, pet/melee)<br><br>Your mileage may vary. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukoraxs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Koraxs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 12:42:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lamedog.freewebspace.com/images/koraxs.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> If you are just trying to improve tailoring then the best place I have found is Crystal Caverns.  (If you can handle it).  I gather 80 SWATCHES in about 4 hours.  (Me and 53 warrior, although at 55 I could have done it alone, but would not have gotten as many).<br><br>I also got 3 Crystalline Robes, a crystal web shield, and 3 pairs of crystalline slippers.  I was able to solo the queen quite easily, although the poison was  rough (Kicked the warriors ass twice).<br><br>If you are solo, or done have Jyll's, EK is great (spawn time on spiders in Guk is 17 minutes, I could kill em all in about 2, both camps). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/02 10:23:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> CC spiders</span><hr size=1> how do you most efficently kill the spiders in CC? Jyll's? seems like they would have too much hp for a one-shot Jyll's kill, Can you just channel through their hits? how many is it safe to do at once? Seems like this method would burn peridots pretty fast for those of us without epic, and since I've only got 1 jyll's spell, there's a long refresh time between casts...<br><br>-Chiriko, lvl 53 channeler, Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthisismal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThisIsMal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/02 9:30:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CC spiders</span><hr size=1> I passively gathered silk from heart spiders in Guk.  I'd just bind there.  When I was in transit from one place to another, I'd gate to Guk, kill them (if camp was open) and go on to wherever I was actually going.<br><br>Still on 5th shawl myself (failed first combine).  Gathering biles has been worst part IMO. <p><img src="http://pages.prodigy.net/lindawhitesell/images/MalodySmall.jpg"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67272>Malody</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthisismal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThisIsMal</A> at: 4/29/02 9:31:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umagatone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magatone</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/02 10:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://userpages.umbc.edu/~eberry1/images/bm3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> For regular silk, I usually just go to uguk and kill all the heart spiders.  I don't like paying enough attention to it to kill the ones in EK.  Is it better or worse?  I don't know.  I get bored faster in EK, so I figure it's about the same either place.<br><br>As for CC and crytalline silk, it's a real pain to solo.  Jyll's works, but you've gotta be willing to take some damage.  When I was doing that, I'd stand as far away from the next spider as I could and draught of fire twice.  I could usually get the second one off before the spider got to me or after like 1 round of it attacking me, and that was enough to kill it.  The drop rate on those silks is horrid though, and I could only get about 1/2 way down the tunnel before mana ran out.  To supplement silk gathering, my friends that hunted in Velks at the time would give me all the crystalline silks that they could collect.  I definitely recommend either having people help you gather the crystalline silks, or auctioning that you're buying crystalline silks everywhere you go. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110011">Magatone Brac'Taur</a><BR>Evoker of the 57th rank<BR>Member of <a href="http://www.eqcotc.com/default.htm">Court of the Crosswinds</a><BR>Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulaenyelmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LaenyelMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/02 11:11:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I took a slightly unconventional approach to get shawl seven.<br><br>For the Wu's phase of the tailoring tradeskill, I got my silks from EK.<br><br>I would alternate spiders (any kind) with snakes (any kind) in HUGE trains after ooc'ing was anyone hunting either and getting no response then warning about the coming madness. Please be considerate of and careful to avoid anyone hunting for experience in the area.<br><br>Run around (jboots) and tag (SoTF) all of either spiders or snakes that you can find (in the general vicinity of the north and south hills near the ramp to HH). Time it right, and Jylls can land on the whole bunch. Then, four try to hit you and the rest wander off, but if you run away from the four, the rest resume following you too. Circle them around and stop in front those carrion spiders that are almost dead. If you time this one right, you'll kill those in run mode and put the rest into or near it. One or two more stops in front of the crags and Jylls will finish their run. Get resisted, interrupted or miss the timing and just circle around and try again. Might want to learn with eight and skin on, though, and any form of clarity is nice.<br><br>By the time I'd combined the one to two stacks of swatches from a run, I'd be about ready for another.<br><br>Only works if they are green enough for you to withstand a minimum of four times the number of Jylls required to kill them, but the awesome carnage is impressive. My own personal AoE group without a cleric or enchanter.<br><br>I must have killed at least two at the same time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br><br>Laenyel<br>Evoker<br>Elven Elite <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaroob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daroob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/02 7:30:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I can safely say that EK is better than Uguk if you want to collect silks fast.  However, if you want to passively farm silks while doing something else (like laundry or reading) head to Uguk because you'll have more downtime.<br><br>In EK, you basically just need to run a circle and you'll see all the spider spawns.  My path was roughly from the gnolls near Highpass, to Squire Wimbly, to the druids, to the merchants huts.  I didn't have a tracker and I still managed to keep a very nice and steady kill rate going.  Crag spiders simply drop more silks per kill which is why EK is the way to go.  I got 6 silks in one kill once.  If you have a bad wave in Uguk you might get 6 silks for your 17 minutes of medding.<br><br>And, KEI doesn't help you in Uguk.  You have more than enough time to med if you PB AoE the three spider camps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucova69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cova 69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/21/02 2:25:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> If you have a bard or chanter to help you - EK wins no contest.  I did this yesterday with my brother (49 bard) and me (58 wiz).  We split the zone in 1/2 at the road that goes from NK to HP - I would run around tagging everything (snakes, wolves, spiders, lions, etc.) I saw with flux-staff, while my brother ran around with his drum going and just punching everything he saw to aggro it (and with bard speed, he could still tag faster than I could with a ranged flux).  When we decided we had enough stuff (read - couldn't find anymore stuff to tag) we'd meet at a pre-determined location (easy to see the train from a LONG way away and to find the other person) and he'd sing AE mez for a couple ticks to get around the aggro limit and get everything nicely bunched up on our heads.  One cast of zephyr of ice would instantly drop everything within cast range.  By the time zephyr refreshed all the stuff that was resisting mez and staying out of aggro range from the aggro limit would now be trying to beat on my brother again (and many would be mez'd again) and a second cast by me would drop the rest.  The remaining two or three mobs he would just chase down and melee to death while I looted.  In about an hour, maybe 1.5 we had gathered near 300 silks, and a good quantity of MQ and HQ lion pelts (destroying ruined and LQ).<br><br>I've done EK solo as well - and spiders definatly share a spawn table with at least a few other mobs in the zone.  When you start mass-AE'ing all the snakes, wolves, lions, and everything else, the spider population increases by a LOT.  we were commonly getting 20+ spiders in a pull, with perhaps 10 minutes between pulls (including looting time)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urochenko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rochenko</A></span><br> <span class